\begin_layout Exercise*
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after "Ex-3.5"
key "aluffi"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 Define in what sense the category constructed in Eg-3.4 coincides with that in Eg-3.3.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution*
Given a set 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

,
 define the relation 
\begin_inset Formula $\sim$
\end_inset

 on 
\begin_inset Formula $\powerset(S)$
\end_inset

 as such:
 any two subsets 
\begin_inset Formula $A,B$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 are related by 
\begin_inset Formula $\sim$
\end_inset

,
 as in 
\begin_inset Formula $A\sim B$
\end_inset

 if and only if 
\begin_inset Formula $A\subseteq B$
\end_inset

.
 The rest is obvious.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution*
Simply put,
 the 
\begin_inset Formula $\subseteq$
\end_inset

 relation is a preorder.
 That is,
 
\begin_inset Formula $A\subseteq A$
\end_inset

 for every susbet 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A\subseteq B,B\subseteq C$
\end_inset

 means 
\begin_inset Formula $A\subseteq C$
\end_inset

 for any subsets 
\begin_inset Formula $A,B,C$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\hfill\blacksquare$
\end_inset


\end_layout

